ak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | Album\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.7em;font-size:85%;\"| [[UK Singles Chart|UK]]<br /><ref name=\"UK\"/>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.7em;font-size:85%;\"| [[UK Rock & Metal Singles and Albums Charts|UK<br>Rock]] <br><ref name=\"UK Rock Singles Chart\">Peak chart position on the UK Rock & Metal Singles Chart:\n* ''Wake Up Call'': {{cite web |url=https://www.officialcharts.com/charts/rock-and-metal-singles-chart/20151023/111/|title=\"Wake Up Call\" Chart Position |website=[[Official Charts Company]] |date=23 October 2015 |accessdate=29 May 2019}}\n* ''Ban all the Music'': {{cite web |url=https://www.officialcharts.com/charts/rock-and-metal-singles-chart/20151023/111/|title=\"Ban all the Music\" Chart Position |website=[[Official Charts Company]] |date=23 October 2015 |accessdate=29 May 2019}}\n* ''Trip Switch'': {{cite web |url=https://www.officialcharts.com/charts/rock-and-metal-singles-chart/20150821/111/|title=\"Trip Switch\" Chart Position |website=[[Official Charts Company]] |date=21 August 2015 |accessdate=29 May 2019}}\n* ''Excuse Me'': {{cite web |url=https://www.officialcharts.com/charts/rock-and-metal-singles-chart/20151023/111/|title=\"Excuse Me\" Chart Position |website=[[Official Charts Company]] |date=23 October 2015 |accessdate=29 May 2019}}\n* ''Amsterdam'': {{cite web |url=https://www.officialcharts.com/charts/rock-and-metal-singles-chart/20170714/111/|title=\"Amsterdam\" Chart Position |website=[[Official Charts Company]] |date=14 July 2017 |accessdate=29 May 2019}}\n* ''Forever & Ever More'': {{cite web |url=https://www.officialcharts.com/charts/rock-and-metal-singles-chart/20181026/111/|title=\"Forever & Ever More\" Chart Position |website=[[Official Charts Company]] |date=26 Oct 2018 |accessdate=29 May 2019}}\n</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.7em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Ultratop|BEL (Fl)]]<br /><ref name=\"FL\"/>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.7em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Canadian rock/alternative chart|CAN<br />Rock]]<br /><ref name=\"Prometheus Global Media\">{{cite web|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/6655328/nothing-but-thieves/chart|title=Nothing But Thieves \u2013 Chart History|accessdate=1 June 2016}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.7em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Mexico Ingles Airplay|MEX<br /> Air.]]<br><ref name=\"MEX\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/biz/search/charts?f[0]=ts_chart_artistname%3ANothing%20but%20Thieves&f[1]=itm_field_chart_id%3A1188&f[2]=ss_bb_type%3Achart_item&f[3]=ss_bb_type%3Achart_item&type=2&artist=Nothing%20but%20Thieves&detail=1|title=Mexico Ingles Airplay|publisher=Billboard.biz}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.7em;font-size:85%;\"| [[MegaCharts|NLD]]<br /><ref>http://acharts.co/artist/nothing_but_thieves#songs</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.7em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Scottish Singles and Albums Charts|SCO]]<br><ref name=\"SCO\">Peak chart positions in Scotland:\n* \"Sorry\": {{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/charts/scottish-singles-chart/20170929/41/|title=Official Scottish Singles Chart Top 100 \u2013 29 September 2017|publisher=[[Official Charts Company]]|accessdate=30 September 2017}}\n* \"Forever & Ever More\": {{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/charts/scottish-singles-chart/20181026/41/|title=Official Scottish Singles Chart Top 100 \u2013 26 October 2018|publisher=[[Official Charts Company]]|accessdate=26 October 2018}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.7em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Alternative Songs|US<br />Alt.]]<br><ref name=\"Prometheus Global Media\"/>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.7em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Mainstream Rock (chart)|US<br />Main.<br />Rock]]<br /><ref name=\"Prometheus Global Media\"/>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.7em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Rock Songs|US<br />Rock Air.]]<br /><ref name=\"Prometheus Global Media\"/>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.7em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Rock Songs|US<br />Rock]]<br /