{"title_page": "Yang Joon-il", "text_new": "{{Korean name|[[Yang (Korean surname)|Yang]]}}\n{{Infobox musical artist  <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject Musicians -->\n| name             = Yang Joon-il\n| image            = Yang_Joon_Il.2019.jpg\n| caption          = \n| image_size       = \n| background       = solo_singer\n| birth_name       = \n| alias            = \n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|1969|8|19}}\n| birth_place      = Vietnam\n| origin           = [[South Korea]]\n| instrument       = \n| genre            = K-pop, New Jack Swing, Ballad, Dance pop\n| occupation       = Singer, Songwriter, Rapper, Producer, Author\n| years_active     = 1991\u20131993 <br/> 2001 (as V2) <br/> 2019\u2013present\n| label            = \n| associated_acts  = \n}}\n{{Infobox Korean name\n| hangul  = {{linktext|\uc591|\uc900|\uc77c}}\n| hanja   = \u6881\u4fca\u65e5\n| rr      = Yang Jun-il\n| mr      = Yang Chun-il\n}}\n\n'''Yang Joon-il''' (born 19 August 1969), also known as '''Joon-il Yang''', '''JIY''' and '''V2''', is a Korean-American singer-songwriter. Nicknamed the \"G-Dragon of the 1990s\", Yang made his debut in 1991 with a song titled \"Rebecca\". He was active in South Korea from 1991 to 1993 before he was banned to perform on TV. He fled back to America disappearing away from the public scene. He recently gained attention through [[JTBC]]'s ''[[Two Yoo Project Sugar Man]]'', a program dedicated to finding and rediscovering old singers from the past.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://hk.entertainment.appledaily.com/enews/realtime/article/20191207/60351939|title=50\u6b72\u97d3\u6b4c\u624b\u649e\u6a23 \u5c01\u300c90\u5e74\u4ee3GD\u300d\u5f15\u95dc\u6ce8|accessdate=23 January 2020|date=7 December 2019}}</ref><ref name=koreatimes>{{cite web|first=Anna J.|last=Park|title=Yang Joon-il, a musician living ahead of his time, finally recognized 30 year later|url=https://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/art/2019/12/682_280113.html|website=[[The Korea Times]]|accessdate=19 January 2020|date=13 December 2019}}</ref><ref name=koreajoongangdaily>{{cite web|last=Yoon|first=So-yeon|title=Fans welcome back Yang Joon-il|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=3072077|website=[[Korea JoongAng Daily]]|accessdate=19 January 2020|date=1 January 2020}}</ref><ref name=yonhap>{{cite web|last=Park|first=Bo-ram|title=Return of long-forgotten singer Yang Joon-il brings middle-aged fans to music scene|url=https://en.yna.co.kr/view/AEN20191231006300315|website=[[Yonhap]]|accessdate=19 January 2020|date=31 December 2019 }}</ref> As of 2020, he is active in various fields such as fan meeting, book writing, public appearances, lectures, commercials, beauty and fashion related activities.\n\n==Personal life==\nYang was born in [[Vietnam]] during the [[Vietnam War|war]] in 1969 and spent his childhood in Hong Kong, Japan, and South Korea.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://star-profile.tistory.com/439|title=\uac00\uc218 \uc591\uc900\uc77c \ud504\ub85c\ud544|date=2019-12-28|website=Star Profile|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref> Yang emigrated to the [[United States]] with his family at age nine and grew up in [[Los Angeles]]. After one year of dating Yang married a woman who fell in love at first sight in 2006 and the first son was born in 2015.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://woman.chosun.com/client/news/viw.asp?cate=C01&mcate=M1001&nNewsNumb=20200264195|title=\uc591\uc900\uc77c\u2026\uc544\ub0b4\uc640 \uc778\uc5f0, \uacb0\ud63c \uc774\uc720 \uccab \uace0\ubc31 \u201c\ud55c\ub208\uc5d0 \ubc18\ud588\ub2e4\u201d|date=2020-02-11|website=woman.chosun.com|language=ko|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n==Career==\nWhen he was in [[Glendale High School (Glendale, California)|Glendale High School]] in LA, he was persuaded to make a debut as an entertainer by the late Hollywood actor [[Soon-Tek Oh|Soon-tek Oh]], who was a member to the same church.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tenasia.hankyung.com/topic/article/2020012937744|title=\u6545 \uc624\uc21c\ud0dd \ub204\uad6c?...\uc591\uc900\uc77c\uacfc \ubbf8\uad6d\uc11c \uae4a\uc740 \uc778\uc5f0 {{!}} \ud150\uc544\uc2dc\uc544|last=tenasia.hankyung.com|first=Digital|date=2020-01-29|website=\ud150\uc544\uc2dc\uc544 \uc5f0\uc608\ub274\uc2a4|language=ko|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref> Yang was a soloist in his high school choir. He took classes at [https://www.jrpowersphilly.com/ John Robert Powers Modeling, Acting Agency & Finishing School] in [[Philadelphia]] to prepare for his debut.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mk.co.kr/star/broadcasting-service/view/2020/02/191812/|title=\u2018\ubc30\ucca0\uc218 \uc7bc\u2019 \uc591\uc900\uc77c, \ubc1c\ub77c\ub4dc \uac00\uc218 \ub370\ubdd4 \ube44\ud558\uc778\ub4dc...\u2018\ub9ac\ubca0\uce74\u2019 \uc5b4\ucfe0\uc2a4\ud2f1 \ubc84\uc804 \uacf5\uac1c[\uc885\ud569]|website=\uc2a4\ud0c0\ud22c\ub370\uc774|language=ko|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref> \n\nHe entered [[University of Southern California]] [[USC Marshall School of Business|Marshall School of Business]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hankookilbo.com/News/Read/201912311633093457|title=[\ucf54\ub9ac\uc544\ud0c0\uc784\uc2a4 \ub274\uc2a4] \uc2dc\uac04\uc5ec\ud589\uc790 \uc591\uc900\uc77c, 30\ub144\uc774 \uc9c0\ub098\uc11c\uc57c \uc778\uc815\ubc1b\ub2e4|date=2020-01-01|website=\ud55c\uad6d\uc77c\ubcf4|language=ko|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref> During his studies, he was selected by Lee Beom-hee, who was the famous composer of the day.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.issueinfact.com/news/articleView.html?idxno=13883|title=\uc591\uc900\uc77c \ub9ac\ubca0\uce74 \uc2e0\ub4dc\ub86c \uc5f4\ud48d \u201c\uc5ed\uc8fc\ud589 \uc544\uc774\ucf58 \uc591\uc900\uc77c \ub204\uad6c?\u201d|date=2019-12-26|website=\uc774\uc288\uc778\ud329\ud2b8|language=ko|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref> Yang dropped out to debut as a singer in Korea in 1990.\n\nYang debuted in 1991 at the age of 22 with a song titled \"Rebecca\". \"Rebecca\" and \"Help me Cupid!\" were performed on the air, but not a big hit. His 2nd full length album was released in 1992. He released other hit songs like \"Dance with Me Miss\" (1992) and \"GaNaDaRaMaBaSa\" (1992).<ref name=\"koreatimes\" /><ref name=\"koreajoongangdaily\" /><ref name=\"yonhap\" />\n\nHe was credited as the first pop musician to introduce Korean audiences to the [[new jack swing]] genre, which was popular in the mid-1980s and early 1990s in the U.S. \n\nActive in South Korea from 1991 to 1993, he suddenly disappeared from the public scene and returned to the U.S. In a 2019 interview with the [[The Korea Times]], he revealed that \"he was hated by many for his unusual looks and songs.\" Some also threw rocks during his performance at an open-air stage. While a 10-year visa he held in Korea as a U.S. national had to be recertified every six months, he was denied an extension to his visa for no reason by an official at the Immigration Office. His nationality as an American also made it hard for him to gain acceptance in South Korea.\n\nIn 2001, he made another debut as JIY, a member of a music band V2, with a third album \"Fantasy\". V2 meant his \"Version 2\". He was in active under the name of JIY instead of his real name, Yang Joon-il. He lied about his age and made a big change in his look.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.news1.kr/articles/?3860343|title='\ubc30\ucca0\uc218 \uc7bc' \uc591\uc900\uc77c, \ud5d8\ub09c\ud588\ub358 \uc778\uc0dd\uc0ac\u2192\uc2e0\ub4dc\ub86c\uc5d0 \ub300\ud55c \uc194\uc9c1 \uace0\ubc31\uae4c\uc9c0(\uc885\ud569)|date=2020-03-02|website=\ub274\uc2a41|language=ko|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref> He hid his true identity as music producers told him he would not make it again due to his previous controversial image in Korea. His new song \"Fantasy\", composed by Valery Gaina of [[Cruise (band)|Cruise]], enjoyed a brief popularity before he finally put an end to his music career. Due to the agency's circumstances, it became impossible to work as a musician and after that he worked as an English teacher for 14 years.  In 2015, he returned to the United States. Because of his age, he had a hard time finding work. He worked as a warehouse worker, office cleaner, and restaurant server.    \n\nIn 2019, he gained attention through [[JTBC]]'s ''[[Two Yoo Project Sugar Man]]'', a program dedicated to finding and rediscovering old singers from the past. He sang \"[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WGIndlf_xU4&t=64s Rebecca]\", [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QU462sGMclc \"GaNaDaRaMaBaSa\", \"Dance With Me Miss\"], and \"Fantasy\". Still slim in figure and soulful in his performance, he dazzled the audience and show hosts.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/art/2020/03/682_280113.html|title=Yang Joon-il, a musician living ahead of his time, finally recognized 30 year later|date=2019-12-10|website=koreatimes|language=en|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref> When asked his next plans amid this viral syndrome, he simply said: \"I don't make any plans; I just focus on fully living every moment. If there's any plans, I hope to live as a humble husband and dad.\" When the show hosts asked him to give a message to 20-year-old himself living 30 years ago, Yang said: \"I know nothing will happen how you want. But don't worry, everything will come out perfectly in the end.\"<ref name=\"koreatimes\" /> After his fame skyrocketed again after his appearance on the show, he quit his job at the restaurant to focus on his entertainment career.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.allkpop.com/article/2019/12/g-dragon-of-the-90s-yang-joon-il-visits-jtbcs-news-room-after-his-surging-popularity-says-he-was-working-at-a-restaurant-in-florida|title='G-Dragon of the 90s' Yang Joon Il visits JTBC's 'News Room' after his surging popularity, says he was working at a restaurant in Florida|website=allkpop|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> \n\nOn December 25, Christmas Day, he appeared on [[JTBC Newsroom]]. He said \"It's like a dream every day\", \"I've been trying to get rid of my prejudice against myself, which is full of my mind as if I had to abandon my unhappiness before I was happy.\"  \"There are no more tears\" Yang said, adding that his powerful fandom, which claims to be a support group, is also a big boost to Yang.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.habkorea.net/celebrity-of-celebrity-yang-joon-il-syndrome-in-korea/|title=Celebrity of celebrity, Yang Joon-il Syndrome in Korea {{!}} HaB Korea.net|date=2019-12-26|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> \n\nOn December 31, Yang met with fans through two official fan meeting events. \"Are you really here to see me?\"he said, tearing up with joy. \"This is my first time. I didn't imagine any of this. I'm so grateful.\"<ref name=\":1\" />  In a press conference at a fan meeting, he revealed that his sole dream of becoming a K-pop star in his 20s was finally accomplished now, at age 50.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.yna.co.kr/view/AEN20191231006300315|title=Return of long-forgotten singer Yang Joon-il brings middle-aged fans to music scene|last=\ubc15\ubcf4\ub78c|date=2019-12-31|website=Yonhap News Agency|language=en|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref>\n\nJust a few days before the fan meeting he shot a commercial with Lotte Home Shopping<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.allkpop.com/article/2019/12/gd-of-the-90s-yang-joon-il-lands-a-lotte-home-shopping-cf|title='GD of the 90's Yang Joon Il lands a Lotte Home Shopping CF|website=allkpop|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref> for the first time in his life. He spent that money to rent an apartment in Korea.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.msn.com/ko-kr/entertainment/news/%ED%95%B4%ED%88%AC4-%EC%96%91%EC%A4%80%EC%9D%BC-%E2%80%9C%EC%83%9D%EC%95%A0-%EC%B2%AB-%EA%B4%91%EA%B3%A0%EB%AA%A8%EB%8D%B8%EB%A3%8C-%EB%B0%9B%EC%95%84-%E9%9F%93%EC%95%84%ED%8C%8C%ED%8A%B8-%EB%B3%B4%EC%A6%9D%EA%B8%88-%EB%A7%88%EB%A0%A8%E2%80%9D/ar-BB1166VA|title=\u2018\ud574\ud22c4\u2019 \uc591\uc900\uc77c \u201c\uc0dd\uc560 \uccab \uad11\uace0\ubaa8\ub378\ub8cc \ubc1b\uc544 \u97d3\uc544\ud30c\ud2b8 \ubcf4\uc99d\uae08 \ub9c8\ub828\u201d|website=www.msn.com|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref>\n\nOn January 3 in 2020, Yang created his account on [[Instagram]].[https://www.instagram.com/jiytime/?hl=ko jiytime] On the 4th, he performed his debut song \"Rebecca\" on [[MBC TV|MBC]]'s \"[[Show! Music Core]]\" after 28 years after his debut.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/art/2020/04/732_281557.html|title=At 50, forgotten Korean-American singer compares to G-Dragon|date=2020-01-08|website=koreatimes|language=en|access-date=2020-04-12}}</ref> Yang appeared himself a [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=buy_iFyS8Hg fan video], a parody of his own 90's fashion style.[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=inogwFkBgY4 interview] JTBC's special feature <Sugar Man, Yang Joon-il, 91.19> aired on the 16th and 23rd. The title of the program is meant to commemorate his debut year, 1991 and 2019 when he was recovered.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hundredkorea.com/en/2020/01/15/jtbc-%ec%8b%a0%eb%85%84-%ed%8a%b9%ec%a7%91-%eb%b0%a9%ec%86%a1-%ec%8a%88%ea%b0%80%eb%a7%a8-%ec%96%91%ec%a4%80%ec%9d%bc-91-19-%ec%a0%84%ea%b2%a9-%ed%8c%8c%ea%b2%a9-%ed%8e%b8%ec%84%b1/|title=JTBC set to air a variety special focused on Yang Joon Il|last=100KOREA|date=2020-01-15|website=100KOREA|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n\nOn Febraury 3, his photo essay [Yang Joon Il Maybe] started a pre-sale. On the first day, over 15,000 copies were pre-sold and it became bestseller. A series of the interviews with the behind-the-scenes of photo shooting for his book was released also.[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=C3qzBsWHvic interview-Question From Yang Joon Il] On the 9th, Yang opened his official YouTube channel, [https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCWagJUPy0iR5Cf8hafiYM-w Official Yang Joon Il]. The number of subscribers has spiked up to over 15K in a single day.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.allkpop.com/video/2020/02/yang-joon-il-opens-up-his-official-youtube-channel|title=Yang Joon Il opens up his official YouTube channel!|website=allkpop|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref> On Valentine's day, on Febraury 14, [Yang Joon Il Maybe] was officially released.  \n\nHe also plans to re-arrange and re-record his old songs to release a repackaged album. After that, he hopes to release new songs.\n\n==Discography==\n\n===Album===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\uaca8\uc6b8 \ub098\uadf8\ub124(1991) - produced by Lee Beom-hee(\uc774\ubc94\ud76c)\n!title\n!written by\n!composed by\n!length\n|-\n|\uaca8\uc6b8 \ub098\uadf8\ub124\n|\uc774\uc0c1\ub9cc\n|Lee Beom-hee(\uc774\ubc94\ud76c)\n|3:29\n|-\n|\ud5ec\ud504 \ubbf8 \ud050\ud54f [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CFemlEChrcE Help me, Cupid!]\n|\uac15\ub355\ud76c\n|Lee Beom-hee(\uc774\ubc94\ud76c)\n|3:46\n|-\n|\uc624\uc6d4\uc758 \uad50\uc815\n|\uad8c\ud61c\uacbd\n|Lee Beom-hee(\uc774\ubc94\ud76c)\n|3:39\n|-\n|\ub9ac\ubca0\uce74 [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=l8VYlZJ0CXc Rebecca] \n|Yang Joon-il(\uc591\uc900\uc77c)\n|Lee Beom-hee(\uc774\ubc94\ud76c)\n|3:58\n|-\n|\uac15\ubcc0\uc758 \ud55c \uc0ac\ub78c\n|\uc774\uc131\ud558\n|Lee Beom-hee(\uc774\ubc94\ud76c)\n|3:50\n|-\n|\uc7ac\uc218\uc0dd\n|\uc774\ub3d9\ud604\n|Lee Beom-hee(\uc774\ubc94\ud76c)\n|4:22\n|-\n|\uc878\uc5c5\uacfc \uc774\ubcc4\uacfc \uce5c\uad6c\n|\uc774\ubc94\ud76c\n|Lee Beom-hee(\uc774\ubc94\ud76c)\n|4:00\n|-\n|So Insane\n|Yang Joon-il(\uc591\uc900\uc77c)\n|Lee Beom-hee(\uc774\ubc94\ud76c)\n|3:48\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Your Backside That Caught My Attention(1993)-Produced by P.B. Floyd\n!title\n!written by\n!composed by\n!arranged by\n!length\n|-\n|Your Backside That Caught My Attention(Do It to Me)\n|Yang Joon-il \n|P.B. Floyd, Jay Mitchell, Michael Johnson\n|\n|3'24\"\n|-\n|Dance with me, \uc544\uac00\uc528(Dance with me, Miss) [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rwQwJiwvTVU M/V]\n|Yang Joon-il\n|P.B. Floyd, Jay Mitchell\n|\n|3'33\"\n|-\n|Party Invitation\n|Yang Joon-il\n|P.B. Floyd, Rafael Cunville\n|\n|4'39\"\n|-\n|\uac00\ub098\ub2e4\ub77c\ub9c8\ubc14\uc0ac(Pass Word)\n|Yang Joon-il\n|P.B